WEBVTT

1
00:00:04.879 --> 00:00:08.049
Looks like they're all asleep.
Maybe I should sneak out of here.

2
00:00:08.216 --> 00:00:11.636
No. Why don't you stay for breakfast.

3
00:00:12.262 --> 00:00:14.055
How do you like your eggs?

4
00:00:14.264 --> 00:00:16.933
- What about your sisters?
- What about them?

5
00:00:18.101 --> 00:00:19.394
Whoa!

6
00:00:20.937 --> 00:00:23.148
Sorry. You okay?

7
00:00:23.732 --> 00:00:26.860
- What are you doing?
- Trying to fix the garbage disposal.

8
00:00:27.027 --> 00:00:30.113
- What are you doing?
- Messing around.

9
00:00:31.990 --> 00:00:34.409
Hey. sorry. I should have told you
I was here.

10
00:00:34.617 --> 00:00:39.456
No. don't be silly. Paige is a big girl.
She can hang out all she wants to.

11
00:00:39.664 --> 00:00:41.750
Not that she does a lot. I mean...

12
00:00:41.958 --> 00:00:44.002
- You can stop now.
- Right.

13
00:00:44.210 --> 00:00:45.920
Hey. you mind if I take a look?

14
00:00:46.421 --> 00:00:47.797
Sure. go ahead.

15
00:00:48.465 --> 00:00:50.133
Okay.

16
00:00:53.803 --> 00:00:55.555
What's wrong with the disposal
anyway?

17
00:00:55.722 --> 00:00:58.266
Not disposing. washer not washing.
Cable not cabling.

18
00:00:58.433 --> 00:01:01.144
- Don't forget the sink upstairs.
- It's next on my list.

19
00:01:01.353 --> 00:01:04.564
- Sounds like fun.
- That's my life. actually. All about fun.

20
00:01:11.321 --> 00:01:14.783
- There you go. It's as good as new.
- He's handy to have around.

21
00:01:14.949 --> 00:01:17.410
Yeah. I thought you didn't use
magic anymore.

22
00:01:17.619 --> 00:01:21.206
Just once in a while. for little things.
Want me to fix the washer?

23
00:01:21.414 --> 00:01:22.791
- Yes.
- No.

24
00:01:22.957 --> 00:01:25.377
Can you guys help me pick out
some earrings?

25
00:01:26.711 --> 00:01:28.838
Hi. I didn't know you were here.

26
00:01:29.422 --> 00:01:32.133
Hey. yeah. We got in late last night.

27
00:01:32.676 --> 00:01:35.136
- I see.
- He fixed the garbage disposal.

28
00:01:35.345 --> 00:01:37.430
- Really?
- Magically.

29
00:01:38.348 --> 00:01:39.974
Really?

30
00:01:43.728 --> 00:01:45.980
Can you help me with my earrings
out here. please?

31
00:01:47.023 --> 00:01:48.400
Sure.

32
00:01:49.651 --> 00:01:51.569
Excuse me.

33
00:01:53.446 --> 00:01:56.825
So how do you like your eggs.
scrambled or over easy?

34
00:01:57.909 --> 00:02:00.704
Okay. listen. was that weird?

35
00:02:00.870 --> 00:02:02.288
Why are you so dressed up?

36
00:02:02.455 --> 00:02:05.083
Because I have a date with Jason.
but that's besides the point.

37
00:02:05.291 --> 00:02:08.378
Didn't Richard lose it the last time
he used magic? I mean. really lose it?

38
00:02:08.586 --> 00:02:11.214
I can assure you that he stayed
in complete control

39
00:02:11.381 --> 00:02:13.133
over the garbage disposal.

40
00:02:13.925 --> 00:02:15.969
It's 7:00 in the morning.
how can you have a date?

41
00:02:16.136 --> 00:02:18.346
Because it's 7 here.
but it's evening in Hong Kong.

42
00:02:18.888 --> 00:02:21.599
Okay. so you're not concerned
about Richard using magic?

43
00:02:21.808 --> 00:02:25.562
Yeah. I am. but I'm more concerned
with Paige being really pissed off

44
00:02:25.729 --> 00:02:27.814
because we butted into
her business again.

45
00:02:27.981 --> 00:02:30.650
Yeah. I know. but we're sisters.
that's what we're supposed to do.

46
00:02:30.817 --> 00:02:34.654
Back to your date. I don't understand.
is Chris orbing you to Hong Kong?

47
00:02:34.863 --> 00:02:36.197
No. we're video conferencing.

48
00:02:36.364 --> 00:02:39.200
We just open our laptops
and there we are. in colour.

49
00:02:39.701 --> 00:02:41.077
In each other's laps.

50
00:02:41.286 --> 00:02:43.705
So do you think we should
talk to Paige about Richard?

51
00:02:43.913 --> 00:02:46.791
- We don't really know him.
- I know we don't.

52
00:02:46.958 --> 00:02:48.877
And neither does she.
That's the problem.

53
00:02:50.587 --> 00:02:53.965
- What. can't I worry?
- From afar. Yeah.

54
00:02:54.299 --> 00:02:57.594
Now. excuse me.
I have to go unclog a sink.

55
00:03:07.771 --> 00:03:10.648
Well. maybe a little magic
couldn't hurt.

56
00:03:20.033 --> 00:03:21.910
Help me!

57
00:03:32.587 --> 00:03:35.131
Okay. so watery lady
pops up from the sink.

58
00:03:35.298 --> 00:03:38.593
- You sure she's not a demon?
- I'm sure she needed help.

59
00:03:38.802 --> 00:03:40.470
- What else did she say?
- That was it.

60
00:03:40.637 --> 00:03:42.472
"Harding Park. pond."
and poof!

61
00:03:47.352 --> 00:03:48.812
Over there.

62
00:04:06.621 --> 00:04:09.416
They're coming! Take this.
it does not belong to them!

63
00:04:45.326 --> 00:04:47.078
I'm liking these odds.

64
00:04:51.499 --> 00:04:52.917
Wuss.

65
00:04:53.793 --> 00:04:55.003
The sword.

66
00:04:56.546 --> 00:04:58.548
The sword is...

67
00:05:00.967 --> 00:05:03.678
Where'd she go?
What did she say?

68
00:05:03.887 --> 00:05:07.098
She said something about the sword.
Where is it?

69
00:05:07.557 --> 00:05:09.601
It's in the stone.

70
00:05:16.066 --> 00:05:18.193
The sword in the stone?

71
00:05:18.401 --> 00:05:21.696
Oh. you gotta be kidding me. right?

72
00:07:08.553 --> 00:07:10.597
Okay. could you maybe
miss the table?

73
00:07:10.764 --> 00:07:13.641
I'm sorry. I've never orbed anything
that heavy before.

74
00:07:13.808 --> 00:07:17.020
- Or that historic.
- Is that glowing?

75
00:07:17.187 --> 00:07:19.898
No. it's the sunroom.
there's a lot of light.

76
00:07:20.106 --> 00:07:22.692
What part of this aren't you getting?
Sword. stone. lady in lake.

77
00:07:22.901 --> 00:07:24.194
It was a pond.

78
00:07:25.362 --> 00:07:28.281
- You think she's from Avalon?
- Yeah. I think she was flushed out

79
00:07:28.448 --> 00:07:31.576
by whoever's after Excalibur.
The maker of kings.

80
00:07:31.743 --> 00:07:35.789
Look. we're not talking about Camelot.
right. because that's not real.

81
00:07:35.997 --> 00:07:38.833
You never believed in King Arthur
and the Knights of the Round Table?

82
00:07:39.042 --> 00:07:42.545
Yes. I did. when I was 7.
And then I grew up.

83
00:07:42.962 --> 00:07:45.507
Yeah. you grew up to be a witch

84
00:07:45.674 --> 00:07:47.759
that fights demons
and silly-looking dragons.

85
00:07:47.967 --> 00:07:50.345
- That's different. that's real.
- And this isn't real?

86
00:07:50.553 --> 00:07:53.348
- What is real are those hooded freaks.
- Who are not gonna give up

87
00:07:53.515 --> 00:07:55.684
- now that the sword's in the open.
- How do you know?

88
00:07:55.892 --> 00:07:59.354
Whoever has Excalibur
is unstoppable.

89
00:08:02.565 --> 00:08:05.110
Okay. there's definitely nothing
in the Book.

90
00:08:05.276 --> 00:08:07.612
Oh. hi. How you doing?

91
00:08:08.738 --> 00:08:10.740
Phoebe. please put a stop
to this nonsense.

92
00:08:10.949 --> 00:08:12.784
- Didn't realise you were here.
- That's okay.

93
00:08:12.951 --> 00:08:14.494
You can talk freely in front of him.

94
00:08:14.661 --> 00:08:16.955
Lord knows.
you've been through enough.

95
00:08:17.997 --> 00:08:20.709
- No. not really.
- Phoebe.

96
00:08:21.543 --> 00:08:23.586
Look. I should probably go.

97
00:08:24.212 --> 00:08:26.923
Don't be ridiculous. You're great.

98
00:08:27.132 --> 00:08:29.551
Okay. anyway. Book. Excalibur?

99
00:08:29.759 --> 00:08:31.011
Yeah. nothing. nada.

100
00:08:31.219 --> 00:08:32.637
- Really?
- Told you.

101
00:08:32.846 --> 00:08:36.099
You know. hey. maybe it's been out
of circulation since ye olden days.

102
00:08:36.266 --> 00:08:38.852
and maybe no Halliwell has ever
come across it before.

103
00:08:39.060 --> 00:08:41.771
Well. we have run across these guys.
executioner demons.

104
00:08:42.105 --> 00:08:45.483
- lower-level badasses for hire.
- Who hired them?

105
00:08:45.650 --> 00:08:48.111
This higher-level badass.

106
00:08:48.528 --> 00:08:51.072
"A power-mad paladin
of destruction."

107
00:08:52.323 --> 00:08:55.660
Maybe... You know. maybe we
should just kind of hang out later.

108
00:08:55.827 --> 00:08:58.955
Yeah. Okay. Bye.

109
00:08:59.164 --> 00:09:00.707
Bye.

110
00:09:03.585 --> 00:09:04.753
I don't know.

111
00:09:05.378 --> 00:09:09.966
- Be careful with all this.
- Always. I had...

112
00:09:10.884 --> 00:09:14.346
...a really good time last night.
- Me too.

113
00:09:15.347 --> 00:09:16.931
What?

114
00:09:17.640 --> 00:09:21.102
I just don't think your sisters
like me very much.

115
00:09:21.311 --> 00:09:23.438
- No. that's not true.
- Really?

116
00:09:23.605 --> 00:09:27.275
Okay. maybe they're just doing
the overprotective sister thing.

117
00:09:28.651 --> 00:09:29.694
Well. that's a good thing.

118
00:09:29.861 --> 00:09:33.156
Because I don't want anything
to happen to you.

119
00:09:33.323 --> 00:09:34.449
Don't worry.

120
00:09:40.288 --> 00:09:42.248
So he's an upper-level demon.
which means

121
00:09:42.415 --> 00:09:45.877
you should be able to make
a vanquishing potion.

122
00:09:46.044 --> 00:09:49.005
Okay. Wait. Me? Why me?

123
00:09:49.172 --> 00:09:52.676
Because. hello. I have a few
hundred things to do

124
00:09:52.842 --> 00:09:54.886
around here. in addition
to raising a small child.

125
00:09:55.053 --> 00:09:56.763
I know. you have so much to do.

126
00:09:56.930 --> 00:09:59.557
You're my hero. But I can't.
I have to go to work.

127
00:09:59.724 --> 00:10:02.102
I still don't have an assistant.
and I'm swamped.

128
00:10:02.268 --> 00:10:03.853
But... Phoebe!

129
00:10:06.189 --> 00:10:08.316
Paige. potion?

130
00:10:08.525 --> 00:10:11.820
Oh. I'm sorry. honey. the temp
agency's already got me a new job.

131
00:10:12.028 --> 00:10:14.447
But that hardly compares with...

132
00:10:14.614 --> 00:10:16.324
Come on. you know
there's a magical reason

133
00:10:16.491 --> 00:10:17.992
that I've had every one
of these jobs.

134
00:10:18.159 --> 00:10:20.036
and who am I to interfere
with destiny?

135
00:10:20.203 --> 00:10:23.707
Okay. so you want me
to add "babysit the sword"

136
00:10:23.873 --> 00:10:27.168
and "mix vanquishing potion"
to my never-ending to-do list.

137
00:10:27.377 --> 00:10:30.005
Look. the sword is stuck
in the stone. You know it. I know it.

138
00:10:30.171 --> 00:10:33.049
the bad guys know it. Nobody's gonna
get it out till King Arthur does.

139
00:10:33.216 --> 00:10:35.218
When that happens.
there'll be lots of fireworks.

140
00:10:35.385 --> 00:10:37.053
- When might that be?
- How should I know?

141
00:10:37.220 --> 00:10:39.264
Maybe a couple thousand years?

142
00:10:49.774 --> 00:10:52.360
Well. you can't blame a girl for trying.

143
00:10:59.951 --> 00:11:01.995
Oh. but I do blame you.

144
00:11:02.203 --> 00:11:05.582
The sword is now locked in stone.
You promised me murderers.

145
00:11:05.749 --> 00:11:08.626
what you delivered
was cannon fodder for witches!

146
00:11:08.835 --> 00:11:10.587
Those weren't just witches.

147
00:11:10.754 --> 00:11:14.090
Tell me. demon. will your thick head
still spout excuses

148
00:11:14.257 --> 00:11:15.925
when it's cut from your neck?

149
00:11:16.134 --> 00:11:18.303
If the sword is
with the Charmed Ones.

150
00:11:18.470 --> 00:11:21.056
it means we need a better class
of executioners. that's all.

151
00:11:24.976 --> 00:11:26.811
And how much more
will this cost me?

152
00:11:27.520 --> 00:11:30.815
- The Charmed Ones are formidable.
- How much?

153
00:11:31.024 --> 00:11:32.776
To provide you
with more executioners

154
00:11:32.984 --> 00:11:36.613
and the training needed to drown the
Charmed Ones in their own blood...

155
00:11:40.408 --> 00:11:43.370
...a seat at the table.

156
00:11:47.248 --> 00:11:51.795
If your goal is to unite all evil under
the corrupted power of the sword.

157
00:11:51.961 --> 00:11:54.589
you could do far worse
than have me at your side.

158
00:12:00.553 --> 00:12:04.140
- Responses to last week's columns.
- How'd you get into my e-mail?

159
00:12:04.307 --> 00:12:07.143
Your e-mail account is maxed out.
so your fans are using ours.

160
00:12:07.644 --> 00:12:11.439
Oh. I'll tell you. Elise better find me
a new assistant because pretty soon

161
00:12:11.606 --> 00:12:15.276
she's gonna have to ask Phoebe
to take my foot out of her...

162
00:12:17.404 --> 00:12:20.073
Hello. Phoebe Halliwell.

163
00:12:20.240 --> 00:12:22.450
Oh. hey. Laura.

164
00:12:22.617 --> 00:12:24.452
I have that down...

165
00:12:25.787 --> 00:12:30.083
...for this morning. Oh. my God.
I missed it. I'm so sorry.

166
00:12:30.250 --> 00:12:33.712
No. of course I can reschedule.
Absolutely.

167
00:12:35.130 --> 00:12:39.384
Actually. Laura. can I call you back
when I have my book in front of me?

168
00:12:39.551 --> 00:12:43.638
Okay. great. I'm so sorry.
Thanks. Bye.

169
00:12:43.847 --> 00:12:47.017
Hi. I thought you had
a new temp job today.

170
00:12:47.225 --> 00:12:49.519
- I do.
- Why aren't you there?

171
00:12:50.020 --> 00:12:51.646
Apparently I am.

172
00:12:52.856 --> 00:12:55.400
- What? Here?
- Yep.

173
00:12:55.567 --> 00:12:57.861
- As my assistant?
- Well. I think I'd prefer

174
00:12:58.028 --> 00:12:59.404
to be called your desk manager.

175
00:12:59.571 --> 00:13:02.824
Wait. but I thought you get all
of your temp jobs for divine reasons.

176
00:13:03.033 --> 00:13:04.159
Usually I do.

177
00:13:04.325 --> 00:13:06.786
Yeah. but I don't need divine help.
I need filing

178
00:13:06.953 --> 00:13:09.330
and faxing
and desk-management help.

179
00:13:09.539 --> 00:13:12.667
I'm your girl. I really am.
We'll just. you know. see if

180
00:13:12.834 --> 00:13:15.170
the divine stuff kind of appears later.
It usually does.

181
00:13:15.670 --> 00:13:19.382
Yeah. but I can't tell you what to do.
I mean. how weird is that?

182
00:13:19.591 --> 00:13:21.301
Well. it's no weirder than usual.

183
00:13:22.385 --> 00:13:24.637
- I see.
- Just kidding. sort of.

184
00:13:24.804 --> 00:13:27.640
Listen. you get back to your column.
I will call Laura and reschedule.

185
00:13:27.807 --> 00:13:29.309
I will...

186
00:13:29.601 --> 00:13:32.228
...help stuff.

187
00:13:45.367 --> 00:13:47.160
Perfect.

188
00:13:58.546 --> 00:14:00.423
Hey. lady!

189
00:14:04.594 --> 00:14:06.888
We could really use
an authority figure out there.

190
00:14:07.972 --> 00:14:10.141
- What are you doing here?
- What am I doing here?

191
00:14:10.308 --> 00:14:12.977
I'm getting pushed around!
I just lost my place in line.

192
00:14:13.186 --> 00:14:14.646
What line?

193
00:14:22.529 --> 00:14:24.781
What...? What's going on here?

194
00:14:29.911 --> 00:14:31.579
Never.

195
00:14:33.289 --> 00:14:35.792
- What is this?
- Natural selection.

196
00:14:35.959 --> 00:14:38.753
Naturally. I hope the sword
selects me to be king.

197
00:14:38.920 --> 00:14:40.922
Finally get a little respect around here.

198
00:14:46.344 --> 00:14:50.932
You people. you creatures. whatever.
You can't be here. You gotta go.

199
00:14:51.141 --> 00:14:53.768
We have a divine right to try our hand.

200
00:14:54.644 --> 00:14:55.895
- Wow.
- Yeah.

201
00:14:56.062 --> 00:14:57.772
Ten feet's pretty much the distance.

202
00:14:58.314 --> 00:15:00.191
Back of the line. please.

203
00:15:00.525 --> 00:15:01.651
Hoof it. sister!

204
00:15:01.860 --> 00:15:05.363
Chris! Chris. Get down here.

205
00:15:06.406 --> 00:15:08.450
- Where's Chris?
- Busy.

206
00:15:08.908 --> 00:15:10.452
Let's go.

207
00:15:10.660 --> 00:15:12.120
- What's going on?
- Busy with what?

208
00:15:12.328 --> 00:15:15.206
Other charges. I took him
off your account again.

209
00:15:15.373 --> 00:15:17.417
- Our account?
- You know what I mean.

210
00:15:19.669 --> 00:15:23.048
- Whoa. is that what I think it is?
- No. No. it's not.

211
00:15:23.214 --> 00:15:25.717
Okay. now look. you gotta get
all these people out of here

212
00:15:25.884 --> 00:15:27.802
because I can't do this right now.

213
00:15:28.011 --> 00:15:30.722
Hey. hey. hey! No cuts. buddy.

214
00:15:37.979 --> 00:15:39.689
Hey. how was the staff meeting?

215
00:15:39.856 --> 00:15:41.649
Endless. How's my new assistant
working out?

216
00:15:41.816 --> 00:15:44.861
Oh. she put a fire under the interns.
that's for sure.

217
00:15:45.028 --> 00:15:46.571
Really?

218
00:15:47.697 --> 00:15:49.240
Okay. who can help me with that?

219
00:15:49.407 --> 00:15:53.119
Great. you got it. And what about
collating and cross-referencing?

220
00:15:53.286 --> 00:15:55.497
You. And so you would
have databasing.

221
00:15:55.663 --> 00:15:58.500
All right. great. You boys
have your marching orders.

222
00:15:58.667 --> 00:16:00.877
I will check back with you
in a couple hours.

223
00:16:04.589 --> 00:16:07.717
Wow. who works here?

224
00:16:07.926 --> 00:16:10.720
You do. Who rocks?
That would be me.

225
00:16:10.929 --> 00:16:13.181
By the end of the day.
we'll have a system in place

226
00:16:13.348 --> 00:16:15.934
that tracks your column ideas.
your columns written

227
00:16:16.101 --> 00:16:17.477
and your columns considered.

228
00:16:17.644 --> 00:16:20.772
plus a separate file for your questions.
comments and fan mail.

229
00:16:20.980 --> 00:16:23.274
- I can't believe it.
- Well. believe it because you.

230
00:16:23.441 --> 00:16:26.403
my dear. are never going to miss
anything again.

231
00:16:26.611 --> 00:16:28.196
- That's good.
- It is good news

232
00:16:28.363 --> 00:16:30.156
because you. my dear.
need to concentrate.

233
00:16:30.323 --> 00:16:31.825
Yes. I do.

234
00:16:31.991 --> 00:16:34.911
Yes. you do.
Starting with tomorrow's column.

235
00:16:35.120 --> 00:16:38.498
- I already wrote tomorrow's column.
- Yeah. you did.

236
00:16:40.959 --> 00:16:42.877
Is there a problem with it?

237
00:16:43.044 --> 00:16:45.130
Well. I mean. I'm no expert.

238
00:16:45.338 --> 00:16:47.424
but I was just thinking
about this one question.

239
00:16:47.590 --> 00:16:50.802
Okay. the girl's family wants her
to break up with him

240
00:16:50.969 --> 00:16:52.512
because they think
he's an alcoholic.

241
00:16:52.679 --> 00:16:54.931
And absent of any proof.
you're telling her to end it.

242
00:16:55.140 --> 00:16:59.602
Well. you know. not really end it.
just slow it down a bit.

243
00:17:00.145 --> 00:17:03.815
Okay. but slowing it down
by not seeing each other is.

244
00:17:03.982 --> 00:17:05.442
in effect. ending it.

245
00:17:05.650 --> 00:17:07.986
I just think you should
keep your eyes open.

246
00:17:08.653 --> 00:17:10.405
Keep my eyes open?

247
00:17:10.613 --> 00:17:13.616
I mean. I think that she should keep
her eyes open.

248
00:17:13.783 --> 00:17:17.245
- You know what I mean.
- Yeah.

249
00:17:18.496 --> 00:17:22.500
- This column's about Richard. isn't it?
- No. it is not about Richard.

250
00:17:22.667 --> 00:17:24.085
Don't be ridiculous.

251
00:17:25.295 --> 00:17:28.798
You hate him. I can tell.
and what's worse. he can tell.

252
00:17:29.007 --> 00:17:32.218
Look. Paige. if you're sensing
anything from me. it's just concern.

253
00:17:32.427 --> 00:17:36.056
I'm concerned that you're falling
too fast for a guy you barely know.

254
00:17:38.099 --> 00:17:40.393
But. you know.
it's none of my business.

255
00:17:40.602 --> 00:17:44.064
You're right. It's not
any of your business.

256
00:17:46.107 --> 00:17:47.692
Right.

257
00:17:49.277 --> 00:17:51.112
Hey. Piper needs your help. now.

258
00:18:03.416 --> 00:18:05.085
Pest.

259
00:18:07.754 --> 00:18:09.547
Oh. my!

260
00:18:09.714 --> 00:18:13.009
- I was afraid this would happen.
- You could have mentioned that.

261
00:18:13.176 --> 00:18:15.679
- And they won't leave?
- Oh. no. No.

262
00:18:15.845 --> 00:18:18.932
- More show up every minute.
- But no bad guys yet. right?

263
00:18:19.099 --> 00:18:21.184
What is that stench?
What is that stench?

264
00:18:21.393 --> 00:18:24.145
We gotta get this thing out
of here. Leo refuses to orb it.

265
00:18:24.354 --> 00:18:26.815
The Lady of the Lake came to you.
I'm not messing with that.

266
00:18:27.023 --> 00:18:31.569
Oh. for God's sakes. if you
will not get rid of it. then I will!

267
00:18:37.701 --> 00:18:38.993
Your Majesty.

268
00:18:40.870 --> 00:18:42.580
Wow.

269
00:18:58.471 --> 00:19:01.099
I bet you didn't expect this
when you got up this morning.

270
00:19:01.307 --> 00:19:04.019
- L...
- The sword has chosen.

271
00:19:05.061 --> 00:19:07.313
You are the new saviour.

272
00:19:07.480 --> 00:19:09.357
The champion of good.

273
00:19:09.524 --> 00:19:11.276
the master of Excalibur.

274
00:19:13.069 --> 00:19:16.197
- Welcome to your new destiny.
- Oh. crap.

275
00:19:18.742 --> 00:19:21.953
Okay. let's go. Nothing to see
here anymore.

276
00:19:22.120 --> 00:19:24.956
- no more show. adiós. scram.
- Your Majesty. seriously.

277
00:19:25.123 --> 00:19:28.293
if you need anything. anything at all.
Castles built. suits of armour.

278
00:19:28.460 --> 00:19:30.879
you name it. I got connections.

279
00:19:34.466 --> 00:19:37.677
Is it just me. or does it still
smell like ogre in here?

280
00:19:37.844 --> 00:19:40.972
I'm telling you. guys.
this is all a big mistake.

281
00:19:42.432 --> 00:19:44.225
- Stop that.
- It's drawn to you.

282
00:19:44.392 --> 00:19:47.395
- just like you're drawn to it.
- Do I look like I'm drawn to it. pal?

283
00:19:47.604 --> 00:19:50.065
- You will be in time.
- No. I don't have time

284
00:19:50.231 --> 00:19:51.274
to play Queen Arthur.

285
00:19:51.900 --> 00:19:56.571
Oh. come on. Piper. have a little fun.
Don't you realise what this means?

286
00:19:56.780 --> 00:19:58.281
One more thing on my to-do list?

287
00:19:58.490 --> 00:20:01.451
No. it means you. my dear.
are the chosen one.

288
00:20:01.659 --> 00:20:04.496
the first in centuries to have
power over the sword.

289
00:20:04.662 --> 00:20:06.122
Tell her all about it. Merlin.

290
00:20:06.956 --> 00:20:10.877
Oh. actually. the name's Mordaunt.
Merlin was just a fairy tale.

291
00:20:12.921 --> 00:20:14.756
But Camelot was not.

292
00:20:15.131 --> 00:20:17.384
And thanks to you. it can rise again.

293
00:20:17.592 --> 00:20:20.845
So. what are you. a wizard.
a sorcerer?

294
00:20:21.054 --> 00:20:24.432
Actually. I'm neither.
I'm just a humble teacher

295
00:20:24.599 --> 00:20:26.267
in service of the sword.

296
00:20:26.476 --> 00:20:28.603
And we must begin
instruction immediately.

297
00:20:28.812 --> 00:20:30.271
before your enemy attacks.

298
00:20:30.480 --> 00:20:31.856
- The Dark Knight.
- You know him?

299
00:20:32.023 --> 00:20:33.525
Yeah. we've already kicked his ass.

300
00:20:33.733 --> 00:20:37.153
And if he shows up again. we have a
vanquishing potion ready and waiting.

301
00:20:37.362 --> 00:20:39.656
- What's in it?
- It's a mandrake variation

302
00:20:39.823 --> 00:20:41.908
with a little bit of griffin's blood.

303
00:20:42.075 --> 00:20:46.162
Good. if you're going up against
a pustulous knave. which you're not.

304
00:20:46.371 --> 00:20:50.041
If you want to fight the Dark Knight
with magic. this is what you need.

305
00:20:51.543 --> 00:20:53.294
I thought you said
you weren't a sorcerer.

306
00:20:53.503 --> 00:20:57.424
I picked up a few things along the way.
The Dark Knight is no trifle.

307
00:20:57.590 --> 00:20:59.634
You'll have to hit him
with everything you have.

308
00:20:59.843 --> 00:21:02.220
I've never even heard of half
of these ingredients.

309
00:21:02.429 --> 00:21:04.389
Looks like he picked up
quite a bit.

310
00:21:06.349 --> 00:21:08.143
What do you think?

311
00:21:10.478 --> 00:21:12.897
- Can't get a read on him.
- Your distrust is expected.

312
00:21:13.064 --> 00:21:15.692
but don't let it blind you.
If I haven't taught Piper

313
00:21:15.859 --> 00:21:19.362
how to master the sword
before the Dark Knight returns.

314
00:21:19.571 --> 00:21:21.364
your survival depends on that potion.

315
00:21:22.157 --> 00:21:24.576
Okay. so where are we supposed
to get the ingredients?

316
00:21:24.784 --> 00:21:29.330
I think I know a place. Leave it to me.
your trusty assistant.

317
00:21:29.914 --> 00:21:32.876
All right. I guess I will go check
with the other Elders

318
00:21:33.043 --> 00:21:35.253
and see what they know.

319
00:21:35.462 --> 00:21:37.255
You want me to take Wyatt?

320
00:21:38.590 --> 00:21:40.425
Piper.

321
00:21:40.633 --> 00:21:42.218
Do you want me to take
Wyatt with me?

322
00:21:42.427 --> 00:21:43.845
Oh. yeah. Sure.

323
00:21:46.973 --> 00:21:48.475
I'll be fine.

324
00:21:51.728 --> 00:21:52.937
En garde!

325
00:21:56.649 --> 00:22:00.320
Not bad.
Better than Arthur's first time.

326
00:22:00.528 --> 00:22:04.240
- Really?
- Now. I'm gonna come in low.

327
00:22:05.825 --> 00:22:09.996
Believe in Excalibur.
Just let it flow through you.

328
00:22:15.460 --> 00:22:18.046
- These are your best?
- The highest quality.

329
00:22:18.213 --> 00:22:20.715
- They'll get the job done.
- They'd better.

330
00:22:20.882 --> 00:22:23.677
If they don't. it's not me
they'll have to answer to.

331
00:22:23.843 --> 00:22:26.554
- I thought you were...
- I serve a greater power.

332
00:22:26.763 --> 00:22:28.515
Whose?

333
00:22:31.851 --> 00:22:33.311
We've got a problem.

334
00:22:35.105 --> 00:22:36.523
Hey!

335
00:22:40.652 --> 00:22:44.406
Well. Should have figured
you'd be after the sword.

336
00:22:44.572 --> 00:22:47.242
- Tell him.
- Kiss my grumpy ass.

337
00:22:48.535 --> 00:22:49.577
Tell him.

338
00:22:51.454 --> 00:22:52.914
You're too late.

339
00:22:53.081 --> 00:22:56.751
Piper Halliwell has Excalibur.
And she's being trained how to use it.

340
00:22:56.918 --> 00:22:59.879
By who? Who's training her?

341
00:23:04.551 --> 00:23:09.764
- Does this change anything?
- It changes everything.

342
00:23:17.689 --> 00:23:22.360
I think we got everything you need.
Plant roots. fungi. herbs.

343
00:23:22.527 --> 00:23:25.655
- creature parts. insects.
- Creature parts?

344
00:23:25.822 --> 00:23:27.323
Fairy wings.

345
00:23:27.490 --> 00:23:29.200
Wait. fairy wings?

346
00:23:29.367 --> 00:23:31.828
Well. I didn't kill them
if that's what you're wondering.

347
00:23:31.995 --> 00:23:33.580
- Then how'd you get them?
- Phoebe.

348
00:23:33.747 --> 00:23:35.874
- What? Fair question.
- Actually. I'm not sure.

349
00:23:36.041 --> 00:23:39.419
My family's been stockpiling this stuff
for years because of the feud.

350
00:23:39.627 --> 00:23:41.629
Yeah. but the feud's over. right?

351
00:23:41.838 --> 00:23:43.590
Hey. you know.
I think we're gonna need

352
00:23:43.757 --> 00:23:46.634
a mortar and pestle for the potion.
do you have one?

353
00:23:46.801 --> 00:23:48.053
Yeah.

354
00:23:50.013 --> 00:23:51.806
What are you doing?

355
00:23:51.973 --> 00:23:53.641
- What?
- You don't have to treat him

356
00:23:53.808 --> 00:23:57.270
- like he's evil.
- Paige. I'm just reacting to what I see.

357
00:23:57.479 --> 00:24:00.940
I mean. how many guys do you
know that stockpile gremlin ears?

358
00:24:01.107 --> 00:24:03.234
Okay. first your not-so-subtle column.
and now this.

359
00:24:03.401 --> 00:24:05.570
Why don't you come out
and admit it? You hate him.

360
00:24:05.779 --> 00:24:08.782
Paige. I don't hate him.
I'm just worried.

361
00:24:08.990 --> 00:24:10.950
Well. don't worry.
I know what I'm doing.

362
00:24:11.117 --> 00:24:13.787
Okay. so are you telling me
that it doesn't bother you at all

363
00:24:13.953 --> 00:24:16.289
that he's using magic again?
Or that he has this...?

364
00:24:16.456 --> 00:24:19.042
This room hidden?

365
00:24:19.250 --> 00:24:23.088
What part of "this is not
your business" are you not getting?

366
00:24:23.254 --> 00:24:26.132
Oh. Paige. I am worried about you.

367
00:24:26.299 --> 00:24:29.052
Okay. just like you were worried
about me when I was dating a demon.

368
00:24:29.219 --> 00:24:33.014
- Richard is not a demon.
- No. I know he's not a demon. Paige.

369
00:24:33.181 --> 00:24:35.266
But he has a dark side
and powerful magic.

370
00:24:35.433 --> 00:24:37.143
And that's a very dangerous
combination.

371
00:24:37.310 --> 00:24:40.730
L... I'm worried about you. okay?
I'm sorry.

372
00:24:44.359 --> 00:24:47.946
- Here.
- Thanks.

373
00:24:49.447 --> 00:24:51.366
Everything all right?

374
00:24:54.744 --> 00:24:56.788
Let's just get this over with.

375
00:25:16.641 --> 00:25:19.144
- You're a quick study.
- You're a good teacher.

376
00:25:20.145 --> 00:25:23.356
So you feel the sword's power?

377
00:25:23.565 --> 00:25:25.734
- Yes.
- How's it feel?

378
00:25:26.818 --> 00:25:27.902
Not bad.

379
00:25:29.904 --> 00:25:32.240
You and Excalibur are becoming one.

380
00:25:33.408 --> 00:25:36.202
Soon. nothing will matter.

381
00:25:36.411 --> 00:25:39.247
Nothing except the desire to rule.

382
00:25:50.258 --> 00:25:51.384
You.

383
00:25:51.593 --> 00:25:54.387
I was wondering when you'd show up.
Take him!

384
00:26:07.442 --> 00:26:11.279
- "Wereboar tusk. one pinch.
- Okay.

385
00:26:11.780 --> 00:26:13.198
Nymph hair. one lock.

386
00:26:13.365 --> 00:26:16.409
Oh. I hope this isn't
from someone we know.

387
00:26:16.910 --> 00:26:20.455
Wraith essence. three drops.

388
00:26:21.206 --> 00:26:25.085
- One. two. three.
- And black poppy.

389
00:26:25.251 --> 00:26:27.962
- one level teaspoon."
- I've never even heard of black...

390
00:26:28.171 --> 00:26:29.464
No!

391
00:26:32.050 --> 00:26:34.135
Phoebe. you okay?

392
00:26:36.471 --> 00:26:40.308
- Richard.
- Wait. watch.

393
00:26:42.102 --> 00:26:45.063
Don't ever mix wraith essence
and black poppy.

394
00:26:45.855 --> 00:26:48.817
- Ever.
- Why would Mordaunt do this?

395
00:26:49.025 --> 00:26:50.527
Because he wants you dead.

396
00:27:15.385 --> 00:27:17.637
- I thought we made a deal.
- I don't need you

397
00:27:17.804 --> 00:27:19.597
to get the sword anymore.

398
00:27:22.225 --> 00:27:24.102
I've got her.

399
00:27:29.524 --> 00:27:31.484
Your assimilation is complete.

400
00:27:32.152 --> 00:27:34.362
You are now one with Excalibur.

401
00:27:34.571 --> 00:27:36.239
Now what?

402
00:27:38.283 --> 00:27:41.077
- It's just us.
- He's not what you think he is.

403
00:27:41.244 --> 00:27:43.580
- He tried to kill us.
- He wants the sword.

404
00:27:44.039 --> 00:27:45.373
But the sword chose me.

405
00:27:45.582 --> 00:27:48.918
No. he's just using you. he wants
the power of the sword for himself.

406
00:27:49.127 --> 00:27:51.796
You're not meant
to control the sword.

407
00:27:52.047 --> 00:27:53.548
But I do control it.

408
00:27:56.051 --> 00:27:57.802
And you don't think I can.

409
00:28:00.013 --> 00:28:01.306
Perhaps we should leave.

410
00:28:02.807 --> 00:28:05.310
- Paige. Paige. Paige. Paige.
- Excalibur!

411
00:28:09.773 --> 00:28:11.775
Don't do that again.

412
00:28:13.443 --> 00:28:15.612
It appears your queen has spoken.

413
00:28:19.532 --> 00:28:22.786
Her Majesty has left the building.

414
00:28:22.994 --> 00:28:24.913
Or Her Madness.

415
00:28:31.711 --> 00:28:34.130
Doesn't look like much of a kingdom.

416
00:28:34.506 --> 00:28:37.342
Well. this is just where it begins.

417
00:28:37.509 --> 00:28:39.969
where you form your inner circle.

418
00:28:40.345 --> 00:28:43.390
Let me guess.
the Knights of the Round Table?

419
00:28:43.556 --> 00:28:45.767
The knights of your Round Table.

420
00:28:46.309 --> 00:28:50.730
You're on a new path now.
a new destiny.

421
00:28:51.523 --> 00:28:55.318
That's good because I was
getting a little bored of the old one.

422
00:28:55.485 --> 00:28:57.696
A world of adventure awaits you.

423
00:28:57.862 --> 00:29:01.324
Warfare. conquest.

424
00:29:01.491 --> 00:29:03.493
Camelot.

425
00:29:04.119 --> 00:29:09.040
- And what exactly is Camelot?
- Whatever you want it to be.

426
00:29:09.249 --> 00:29:11.543
It's your kingdom to make.

427
00:29:11.710 --> 00:29:13.753
Could you be a little more specific?

428
00:29:14.713 --> 00:29:18.925
There will be no one above you.
no one to challenge you.

429
00:29:19.134 --> 00:29:22.137
You will have free rein
to reshape the way things are.

430
00:29:22.345 --> 00:29:25.807
to create a world of your dreams.

431
00:29:26.641 --> 00:29:29.853
All will bow down before you.

432
00:29:30.061 --> 00:29:32.480
All will serve your every desire.

433
00:29:33.023 --> 00:29:36.985
- Including you?
- Especially me. my queen.

434
00:29:56.129 --> 00:29:57.922
What is it?

435
00:30:00.008 --> 00:30:01.968
Well. we must...

436
00:30:02.469 --> 00:30:04.262
...build your kingdom first.

437
00:30:04.429 --> 00:30:08.767
And to do that. we need to fill
your Round Table with knights.

438
00:30:10.143 --> 00:30:12.729
- Very well. I have a few ideas.
- No.

439
00:30:14.439 --> 00:30:18.109
Let me be your counsel.
I know best who will serve you well.

440
00:30:18.276 --> 00:30:19.861
But they will not come easily.

441
00:30:20.070 --> 00:30:23.615
You must challenge them
on fields of battle.

442
00:30:23.823 --> 00:30:25.617
Force them to join you.

443
00:30:34.250 --> 00:30:36.711
I think I can do that.

444
00:30:43.677 --> 00:30:47.097
- Anything?
- Nope. can't find Piper anywhere.

445
00:30:47.263 --> 00:30:49.933
Well. Keep looking. she's bound
to show up somewhere.

446
00:30:50.100 --> 00:30:51.768
- Yeah. to do what?
- I don't know.

447
00:30:51.935 --> 00:30:55.063
I don't understand. If she wasn't
supposed to pull the sword out.

448
00:30:55.230 --> 00:30:57.649
- then why was she able to?
- According to the other Elders.

449
00:30:57.816 --> 00:31:01.069
she was only meant to pass it on
to whomever it was really meant for.

450
00:31:01.277 --> 00:31:04.698
So she's not the new King Arthur.
but she is the new Lady of the Lake?

451
00:31:04.906 --> 00:31:07.867
- Basically. yeah.
- Well. why is it turning her evil?

452
00:31:08.076 --> 00:31:10.704
Because only the ultimate power
on Earth can handle Excalibur.

453
00:31:10.870 --> 00:31:12.455
That's why the lady
stayed in the lake.

454
00:31:12.622 --> 00:31:14.416
to insulate herself
from the sword's power.

455
00:31:14.624 --> 00:31:17.419
Okay. so we should find Piper
and then drown her.

456
00:31:18.712 --> 00:31:20.839
- Oh. I'm just kidding. Leo.
- It's no joke.

457
00:31:21.006 --> 00:31:24.134
It's the only way to keep the power
from consuming her. destroying her.

458
00:31:25.510 --> 00:31:27.721
Still. what does Mordaunt
want with Piper?

459
00:31:27.887 --> 00:31:31.224
I mean. he's tricky. but he's hardly
the ultimate power on Earth.

460
00:31:31.433 --> 00:31:33.351
But he can use Piper
to become that power.

461
00:31:36.271 --> 00:31:37.981
Guess who just surfaced.

462
00:31:45.947 --> 00:31:49.117
- Should I kill him?
- You're the queen.

463
00:31:49.492 --> 00:31:52.287
I need one more knight
to sit at my Round Table.

464
00:31:52.454 --> 00:31:56.374
- Care to join me?
- Join you? Which side are you on?

465
00:31:56.541 --> 00:31:59.836
All we're interested in
is the greatest power.

466
00:32:00.003 --> 00:32:01.421
Become one of us.

467
00:32:03.131 --> 00:32:05.342
- What he said.
- What do I get out of it?

468
00:32:05.508 --> 00:32:07.552
You? You get to live.

469
00:32:09.137 --> 00:32:11.306
- Piper!
- I should have known it was a trap!

470
00:32:12.307 --> 00:32:16.186
- You stay put. You. I warned you.
- Sorry. Your Majesty.

471
00:32:17.937 --> 00:32:20.315
Paige. now. orb her.

472
00:32:27.405 --> 00:32:31.910
Impressive. huh?
Now. make your queen proud.

473
00:32:39.376 --> 00:32:40.877
- What just happened?
- I don't know.

474
00:32:41.044 --> 00:32:42.671
but I don't think it's good.

475
00:32:48.009 --> 00:32:49.719
Leo!

476
00:32:54.724 --> 00:32:56.017
Welcome.

477
00:32:56.184 --> 00:32:58.770
I assume you're all wondering
why you've been gathered here.

478
00:32:58.937 --> 00:33:03.024
But don't worry. if I wanted to kill you.
I would have done so already.

479
00:33:03.191 --> 00:33:07.278
You are the chosen few
who will help chart a new world order.

480
00:33:07.445 --> 00:33:09.364
united under me.

481
00:33:09.572 --> 00:33:12.659
Excuse me. Your Majesty.
we're getting ahead of ourselves.

482
00:33:12.826 --> 00:33:16.705
- Are we?
- The small matter of the loyalty oath.

483
00:33:18.123 --> 00:33:20.667
Yeah. That's right.

484
00:33:21.209 --> 00:33:24.337
- Administer that oath.
- Yes. Your Majesty.

485
00:33:24.504 --> 00:33:27.757
If you will all put
your left hand...

486
00:33:29.467 --> 00:33:31.219
...or claw

487
00:33:31.386 --> 00:33:34.180
on one of the five points
of the pentagram in front of you.

488
00:33:47.652 --> 00:33:51.364
Supreme demonic powers.
leave your hosts!

489
00:33:51.740 --> 00:33:55.118
And find a new home
in this willing heart!

490
00:33:56.036 --> 00:33:57.454
What are you doing?

491
00:33:57.746 --> 00:33:59.622
Stop!

492
00:34:13.762 --> 00:34:16.097
You vanquished all my knights. Why?

493
00:34:21.603 --> 00:34:24.814
Fulfilling my centuries-old quest...

494
00:34:25.482 --> 00:34:27.650
...to control Excalibur.

495
00:34:28.234 --> 00:34:31.738
- But it belongs to me.
- No. It doesn't.

496
00:34:33.073 --> 00:34:36.076
It never did. But thanks to you

497
00:34:36.242 --> 00:34:39.079
and the combined powers
of your knights.

498
00:34:39.245 --> 00:34:40.955
now it belongs to me.

499
00:34:42.332 --> 00:34:44.084
I'm the ultimate power.

500
00:34:45.251 --> 00:34:46.628
I don't understand.

501
00:34:47.796 --> 00:34:50.382
It's simply a transfer of power.
that's all.

502
00:34:50.590 --> 00:34:52.592
And now all that remains
to do...

503
00:34:53.176 --> 00:34:56.137
...is to eliminate the true recipient
of Excalibur

504
00:34:56.304 --> 00:35:00.225
before he grows old enough
to fulfil his destiny

505
00:35:00.392 --> 00:35:03.144
as the son of a Charmed One.

506
00:35:04.437 --> 00:35:07.273
You can't hurt him. he's protected.

507
00:35:09.192 --> 00:35:10.652
I couldn't before.

508
00:35:12.320 --> 00:35:14.614
But I can with this.

509
00:35:31.006 --> 00:35:32.590
Feeling any better?

510
00:35:32.757 --> 00:35:37.679
No. I'm pretty sure "ow" signifies that
I am not. in fact. feeling any better.

511
00:35:39.139 --> 00:35:43.059
I am getting tired of this whole
soul-separating-from-my-body thing.

512
00:35:43.226 --> 00:35:44.978
It's getting to be a disturbing pattern.

513
00:35:45.186 --> 00:35:48.523
It was pretty close too. Your souls
were getting ready to move on.

514
00:35:48.690 --> 00:35:51.443
- Move on to where exactly?
- Nice try.

515
00:35:53.069 --> 00:35:55.363
I can't believe Piper.
Did you see the look in her eyes?

516
00:35:55.572 --> 00:35:58.700
Hey. at least it looked like
she was having fun for once.

517
00:35:59.492 --> 00:36:01.244
- Find her yet?
- No. nothing.

518
00:36:01.411 --> 00:36:04.748
Keep trying. Just like last time. they
can't do anything until they resurface.

519
00:36:04.914 --> 00:36:07.542
Yeah. unless Mordaunt wants her
to help him rule the underworld.

520
00:36:07.959 --> 00:36:10.462
There's gotta be another way
to get her out of this.

521
00:36:10.670 --> 00:36:12.922
I just wish we knew
who King Arthur is.

522
00:36:13.631 --> 00:36:16.384
- Wait. what do you mean?
- I mean. if we need to separate

523
00:36:16.551 --> 00:36:18.887
Piper from the sword.
what better way than figure out

524
00:36:19.054 --> 00:36:20.889
who she's meant to give it to?

525
00:36:25.226 --> 00:36:26.770
No.

526
00:36:28.146 --> 00:36:31.316
It's Wyatt. Oh. my God.
It has to be.

527
00:36:33.860 --> 00:36:35.820
- What's the matter?
- It's Piper. she's hurt.

528
00:36:38.823 --> 00:36:41.284
- Harding Park. Let's go.
- I got Wyatt.

529
00:36:46.623 --> 00:36:50.752
Don't worry. it'll all be over soon.

530
00:36:50.960 --> 00:36:53.630
Once they come for you.
I'll go for him.

531
00:36:57.092 --> 00:36:59.010
- Hurry! Hurry. hurry!
- I am. I am.

532
00:37:04.391 --> 00:37:05.684
Where's Wyatt?

533
00:37:13.108 --> 00:37:15.610
My apologies. King Wyatt.

534
00:37:15.819 --> 00:37:18.822
I guess it just wasn't meant to be.

535
00:37:28.456 --> 00:37:30.083
What?!

536
00:37:31.001 --> 00:37:33.253
And that's his favourite teddy bear.

537
00:37:38.216 --> 00:37:39.884
Hey.

538
00:37:41.761 --> 00:37:44.222
Bet you didn't expect this
when you got up this morning.

539
00:37:44.681 --> 00:37:46.599
But I've still got Excalibur!

540
00:37:46.808 --> 00:37:48.852
- Not for long.
- Go for it. Wyatt.

541
00:38:13.376 --> 00:38:17.422
Okay. sweetie.
that's very. very good.

542
00:38:18.006 --> 00:38:23.261
But we need to put this away
so you don't put an eye out.

543
00:38:23.428 --> 00:38:25.597
At least until you're 18.

544
00:38:35.273 --> 00:38:36.483
How are you?

545
00:38:36.900 --> 00:38:40.362
Oh. fine. Think you can orb this
into the attic?

546
00:38:40.570 --> 00:38:42.238
Absolutely.

547
00:38:45.450 --> 00:38:47.702
Away from any furniture?

548
00:38:50.330 --> 00:38:51.414
Sorry.

549
00:38:52.040 --> 00:38:54.042
Don't worry.
I'll just add it to my list.

550
00:39:10.433 --> 00:39:13.895
Hey. I just finished the last of the filing.

551
00:39:14.312 --> 00:39:17.649
- Great. thanks.
- Is that tomorrow's copy?

552
00:39:17.816 --> 00:39:20.151
Yeah. I'm just doing some
last-minute changes.

553
00:39:20.318 --> 00:39:23.988
This woman right here
is worried that her mother

554
00:39:24.155 --> 00:39:26.116
- might be marrying the wrong guy.
- Really?

555
00:39:26.282 --> 00:39:28.451
Yeah. she thinks he might be
the devil incarnate.

556
00:39:28.660 --> 00:39:31.204
Didn't we vanquish
the devil incarnate?

557
00:39:32.122 --> 00:39:34.040
I told her

558
00:39:34.207 --> 00:39:37.877
that unless she has absolute proof.
she should probably butt out

559
00:39:38.044 --> 00:39:39.963
and let her sister live her own life.

560
00:39:40.171 --> 00:39:43.508
- I thought this was about a mother.
- Yeah. well. you know what I mean.

561
00:39:43.717 --> 00:39:44.843
Yeah. I think I do.

562
00:39:45.010 --> 00:39:48.972
It's funny. this is the first job I've gotten
without a magical reason behind it.

563
00:39:49.180 --> 00:39:52.183
Well. there may not have been
a magical reason.

564
00:39:52.350 --> 00:39:53.810
but there was definitely a reason.

565
00:39:55.562 --> 00:39:57.689
I just have to learn
to take my own advice.

566
00:39:57.856 --> 00:40:01.192
Yeah. well. don't stop
worrying about me too much.

567
00:40:01.526 --> 00:40:02.819
Okay.

568
00:40:03.945 --> 00:40:08.283
Hey. sorry to interrupt.
You ready to go?

569
00:40:08.450 --> 00:40:11.327
Yeah. We're going out.
Do you wanna join?

570
00:40:11.536 --> 00:40:14.873
I would love to. actually.

571
00:40:15.040 --> 00:40:17.334
but I'm gonna take a rain check.
It's been a long day.

572
00:40:17.542 --> 00:40:18.585
Okay. Good night.

573
00:40:22.922 --> 00:40:24.883
Hey. Paige.

574
00:40:25.091 --> 00:40:29.637
- you're fired.
- Actually. I quit.

575
00:40:51.326 --> 00:40:53.620
Listen. I want you to promise me

576
00:40:53.787 --> 00:40:56.623
that before we take that thing
out of storage.

577
00:40:56.790 --> 00:40:59.709
that you're gonna play lots
of football and baseball

578
00:40:59.876 --> 00:41:04.381
and have lots of normal toys.
and maybe we'll even get a dog.

579
00:41:04.547 --> 00:41:06.174
What do you think?

580
00:41:07.342 --> 00:41:09.219
How we doing?

581
00:41:09.719 --> 00:41:12.931
His Highness seems content.

582
00:41:13.682 --> 00:41:15.975
- What about you?
- I'm doing all right.

583
00:41:16.142 --> 00:41:19.062
At least I have my priorities straight
now. I was so busy doing stuff.

584
00:41:19.229 --> 00:41:21.314
and all I really wanted to do
was hang out with him.

585
00:41:22.607 --> 00:41:25.026
Well. you should have more time
for that now.

586
00:41:26.444 --> 00:41:28.279
- I fixed the washer.
- You did?

587
00:41:28.446 --> 00:41:33.660
And the sink and the cable
and the toilet.

588
00:41:33.827 --> 00:41:38.206
Wow. I forgot how handy you were
to have around the house.

589
00:41:42.293 --> 00:41:44.004
Pretty strange. huh?

590
00:41:45.588 --> 00:41:47.215
Kind of scary. actually.

591
00:41:47.424 --> 00:41:49.426
- Why?
- Well. we've seen what he can do

592
00:41:49.592 --> 00:41:53.054
without the sword. I can't begin
to imagine what he could do with it.

593
00:41:53.930 --> 00:41:56.057
Well. whatever it is.
it's meant to be.

594
00:41:56.266 --> 00:41:59.853
Doesn't make it
any less scary. though.

595
00:42:00.020 --> 00:42:03.690
But that's tomorrow's problem.
I'll worry about it then.

596
00:42:03.857 --> 00:42:06.026
Okey-dokey.
